The President spoke to a group of governors, expressing his gratitude for their leadership and discussing the importance of the American Rescue Plan. He highlighted the need to combat violent crime, bring back workers to better jobs with better pay and working conditions, and invest in education and childcare. The President also emphasized the importance of rebuilding infrastructure and creating a well-trained and diverse workforce. He mentioned specific states that are already using funds from the American Rescue Plan for these purposes. The President also touched on the challenges of the pandemic, including the need to keep schools open and address the reasons why people are leaving their home countries. He concluded by taking questions from the governors.